If you have any issues with this,
Carol right here would be happy to further assist you.
Oh, great. I see you met your Union rep.

Come on, Bud.
Sir, please.
That new girl's a smoke show.

translation.en: That's why I need you out there with him. Right? Someone who knows the codes to the letter.
translation.es: Por eso debes ir allí afuera con él. Alguien que conozca los códigos.

translation.en: - Okay, but-- - Hey, hey, hey.
Do you wanna move up here?
You gotta get your ass out in the field. All right?
Think about it this way, you're gonna be my eyes and ears, my friend.
translation.es: Piénsalo así. Serás mis ojos y oídos, amigo.

translation.en: - Right? - Right--
And the minute he messes up, the minute he goes against code,
translation.es: Y en cuanto la cague, en cuanto infrinja un código,

The sooner he fucks up, the sooner your sweet cheeks are in Carol's desk.
translation.es: Cuanto antes la cague, antes estarás en el escritorio de Carol.

translation.en: You work out?
- A little. - Yeah, thought so.
You're late.
Close it.
I was actually here an hour ago, but you weren't, so I went to go get us breakfast.
translation.es: Llegué hace una hora, pero no estabas, así que fui por el desayuno.

translation.en: I got you an organic, gluten- free, paleo bran muffin.
translation.es: Te traje una magdalena orgánica paleo libre de gluten.

translation.en: Really? Thank you.
- I was starving. - That was a six- dollar muffin.
translation.es: - Me moría de hambre. - Me costó $6.

- What are you wearing? - Just, like, normal clothes.
The handbook says blend in on the hunt. Be inconspicuous.
translation.es: Según el manual, hay que pasar desapercibido.

translation.en: You have on a suit. How's that inconspicuous?
You have on a suit. We're in the Valley. In the summertime.
translation.es: Un traje en el Valle en pleno verano.

translation.en: - It's a summery suit. - A summery suit?
- Juniper green. Yes. - What is juniper green?
A hue of green I found to be complementary against my skin tone.
translation.es: Un verde que complementa mi tono de piel.

translation.en: Whatever it is, don't wear it again.
Look, I'll put myself together, and we'll take off, all right?
translation.es: Termino con esto, y nos vamos, ¿sí?

Not there.
I'll just… hold on to it.

Got enough weapons and ammo in here to take down El Jefe, huh?
translation.es: Tienes armas y municiones para acabar con El Jefe.

Oh, come on. Legendary 700- year- old European vampire.
translation.es: Vamos. Un vampiro europeo legendario de 700 años.

translation.en: Some say he's at the top of the LA drug trade, just waiting for his moment to reemerge.
translation.es: Dicen que es el capo de la droga y que espera el momento para resurgir.

translation.en: Fangs so sharp, with just one, you could buy a mansion in Bel Air.
translation.es: Con uno de sus colmillos, te compras una mansión en Bel Air.

translation.en: You sound like Big John.
Whole lot of gibberish. You know that's a crock of shit, right?
translation.es: Puras tonterías. Sabes que es una sarta de idioteces, ¿no?

translation.en: I didn't take you for an arts and crafts guy.
translation.es: No sabía que hacías manualidades. ¿Qué es eso?

translation.en: - What are these all about? - Wanna keep your hands off my shit?
translation.es: No sabía que hacías manualidades. ¿Qué es eso? No toques.

translation.en: It's my trophy case.
For each one that I kill, I, uh… They're already dead, but you get my drift.
translation.es: Por cada uno que mato… Ya están muertos, tú me entiendes.

translation.en: 'Cause they're allergic to wood. Smart.
translation.es: Son alérgicos a la madera. Muy listo.

translation.en: They're allergic to wood, but not just any wood. It's mpingo wood.
translation.es: Sí, pero no a cualquiera. Mpingo.

translation.en: The strongest African hardwood. Not that Ikea shit.
translation.es: La más fuerte de África. No esa mierda de IKEA.

translation.en: We mix it with the garlic. The wooden bullets pierce the heart.
translation.es: Con ajo, las balas de madera perforan el corazón.

translation.en: - The silver-- - Silver to the throat. Right.
translation.es: - La plata… - Va a la garganta.

translation.en: Yeah. Cuts the head off… usually.
Usually. Right, you are referring to Uber Vamps,
translation.es: Generalmente. Te refieres a los Vampiros Uber,

translation.en: who have come back from decapitation.
Not if you blast the heart with wood before you cut their throats with silver.
translation.es: No si les metes madera en el corazón antes de decapitarlos con plata.

translation.en: Mm- hmm. You also forgot to mention that you can kill them by burning them.
translation.es: Olvidaste mencionar que puedes matarlos quemándolos.

translation.en: I didn't forget anything. That's how I get my money.
translation.es: No lo olvidé. Así gano dinero.

translation.en: Why would I burn the fangs? I don't do that.
translation.es: ¿Por qué quemar los colmillos? Yo no hago eso.

translation.en: Listen, Guacamole Suit,
right there on the shelf, grab that for me.
Get that, we'll take off.
And remember, whatever you do, don't… drop my shit.
translation.es: Y recuerda, hagas lo que hagas, no tires mis cosas.

translation.en: So, uh, where we going?
I'm going hunting. I don't know about you.
translation.es: Yo voy de cacería. No sé tú.

translation.en: Why you wearing the seat belt like that?
I mean, usually the seat belts aren't like this complicated and heavy. But--
translation.es: Generalmente, los cinturones no son tan complicados y pesados.

translation.en: It's not complicated. It's just a seat belt. It protects you.
translation.es: No es complicado. Es un cinturón. Te protege.

translation.en: Sure.
Sure. It's still protecting me though. If anything happened, it's just--
translation.es: Claro. Igualmente me protege. Si pasara algo…

translation.en: See? It still catches me.
I see.
It's gonna be a long day.
translation.es: Va a ser un día muy largo.

translation.en: So, are you gonna tell me what we're doing at an animal shelter?
translation.es: ¿Me dirás qué hacemos en un refugio de animales?

What you know about Juvies?
Juvies or Juveniles, AKA Zombie Vamps,
translation.es: Juvies o Jóvenes, también Vampiros Zombies,

translation.en: formed when an already young vamp turns somebody else.
translation.es: cuando a alguien lo convierte un vampiro joven.

translation.en: Instead of the strength of a full vamp,
translation.es: No tienen la fuerza del vampiro común,

translation.en: they lack regenerative abilities and appear more dead than alive.
translation.es: no se regeneran y parecen más muertos que vivos.

translation.en: They can't process human blood yet, so what do they do?
translation.es: Aún no procesan la sangre humana, y ¿qué hacen?

translation.en: - I'm aware. - They feed off of small animals, rodents.
translation.es: - Lo sé. - Buscan animales pequeños, roedores.

translation.en: So you've read the book?
I don't have to read it. I'm out here.
translation.es: No me hace falta. Estoy aquí afuera.

translation.en: What do you know about different species of vampires?
I know there are five types. Southern, Eastern, Spider, Uber, and Juvenile.
translation.es: Hay cinco especies. Sureños, Del Este, Arañas, Ubers y Juveniles.

translation.en: They are largely solitary, but when together, there is a hierarchy.
translation.es: Son solitarios, pero juntos, hay cierta jerarquía.

translation.en: They organize by age. What else?
The sunlight is the only thing they're scared of.
translation.es: Solo le temen a la luz solar.

translation.en: They can't reproduce, but they can turn people. Should I continue?
translation.es: No se reproducen, pero pueden convertir gente. ¿Sigo?

translation.en: - What about familiars? - You think this guy's one of them?
translation.es: - ¿Y los familiares? - ¿Crees que este es uno?

translation.en: I don't know. You tell me.
- Hmm? - I think he fits the profile.
- You think so? - Absolutely.
More powerful vamps have more powerful familiars.
translation.es: Los más fuertes tienen familiares más fuertes.

translation.en: And when it comes to Juvies, a little kid like this,
translation.es: Y en cuanto a los Juvies, un chico como ese

translation.en: he's probably grabbing those cats for 'em, try to get 'em turned.
translation.es: debe buscarles gatos, para que los conviertan.

translation.en: - Oh man. - What?
No, I'm just a big cat lover. I got two of them myself.
translation.es: No, amo a los gatos. Tengo dos.

translation.en: Well, that explains it.
- Want to see a picture? - No, I don't.
Maybe later.
All right. Here we go.
There's his car.
Canoga Bowl. Closed for 18 months.
translation.es: Bolera de Canoga, cerrada por 18 meses.

translation.en: It's perfect.
- Can I offer some advice? - No.
I mean, economically speaking, why go after Juvies?
translation.es: Pensando en lo económico, ¿por qué ir por los Juvies?

translation.en: Why not let them ripen, come back when their teeth are valuable?
translation.es: ¿Por qué no volver cuando sus dientes valgan más?

translation.en: I could come back in September, but right now, I'm out of time.
translation.es: Podría volver en septiembre, pero tengo prisa.

translation.en: And beggars can't be choosers.
Plus, you don't want these things biting people, do you?
translation.es: Además, no queremos que muerdan a nadie.

translation.en: Wait. Why don't you have time?
- Why you ask me so many questions? - I'm just--
Just stay in the truck and do your business.
Stay in the truck? No, I have to be with you at all times in the field.
translation.es: ¿En la camioneta? No, debo estar a tu lado en todo momento.

translation.en: - Union rules. - Other than keeping you alive,
translation.es: Son las normas. Me importan una mierda.

translation.en: I don't give a shit about rules.
No, no, you don't understand. All times.
You're gonna stay in this car. With that in mind, here.
translation.es: Te vas a quedar en el auto. Y toma esto.

translation.en: - What? No, I don't believe in guns. - You don't believe in 'em?
translation.es: - ¿Qué? No creo en las armas. - ¿No crees en las armas?

translation.en: No, they're amoral. They're killing machines. They're not for me.
translation.es: No, son amorales. Máquinas asesinas. No son para mí.

translation.en: When I was a kid, I tried shooting a squirrel with a BB gun,
translation.es: De niño, intenté dispararle a una ardilla

translation.en: and I just couldn't. All right?
I still have nightmares where I can see his little face
translation.es: Aún tengo pesadillas en las que veo su cara

translation.en: making little squirrel noises, and I still have nightmares about it.
translation.es: haciendo ruidos de ardilla, y aún tengo pesadillas.

translation.en: Made squirrel noises, huh?
- What does a squirrel noise sound like? - It's like…
Whatever! I don't wanna talk about it.
translation.es: ¡Como sea! No quiero hablar de eso.

translation.en: Stay in the truck.
It's impossible.
How the hell can you be here? It's daytime.
translation.es: ¿Cómo puedes estar aquí? Es de día.

translation.en: You've been a bad boy, Troy.
Did you know that a vampire cannot live without its fangs?
translation.es: ¿Sabías que un vampiro no puede vivir sin colmillos?

translation.en: And yet, for whatever reason, whatever cruel joke from the gods…
translation.es: Por alguna razón, una broma cruel de los dioses…

translation.en: they are the one thing we cannot regenerate.
translation.es: son lo único que no podemos regenerar.

translation.en: Everything that makes a vampire a predator
translation.es: Lo que convierte a un vampiro en depredador

translation.en: is in its fangs.
Each set is a life that could have lived a thousand lives.
translation.es: Cada par es una vida que podría haber vivido 1000 vidas.

translation.en: Lives that you had a part in ending.
Yet it wasn't always like this, you know?
There was a time when you humans, you worshiped us as gods.
translation.es: Antes, los humanos nos veneraban como a dioses.

translation.en: Right here in this valley, you built temples of blood and bone to honor us.
translation.es: En este valle, construyeron templos de sangre y hueso para honrarnos.

translation.en: And then you turned on us.
translation.es: Y luego se volvieron en contra.

translation.en: Well, guess what?
I'm gonna take back what's ours,
one property at a time.
The way I see it, you have two choices, two doors.
translation.es: En mi opinión, tienes dos opciones, dos puertas.

translation.en: One, you bend the knee and join me in service, and you live.
translation.es: Una, te arrodillas y me sirves, y sigues con vida.

translation.en: And two…
you don't.
All right. So, what the hell do you want? Huh?
Who brought you this tooth?
A name.
You're so full of shit, lady.
You think you're a god?
You're not gods. You're a big mistake.
translation.es: No lo son. Son un gran error.

translation.en: You're a genetic mutation that would've died out
translation.es: Una mutación genética que habría muerto

translation.en: if there hadn't been a stinking hole for y'all to crawl into.
translation.es: si no hubieran encontrado un pozo apestoso donde esconderse.

translation.en: Door number two it is.
No. No!  No!
Time for the tooth fairy.
Hello, sir.
How are we on this fine morning?
Any violations to report?
He is certainly heading that way,
but nothing verified quite yet.

translation.es: Me dejó en el auto y entró en una bolera.

translation.en: You didn't follow him?
I thought he was gonna shoot me! He's very difficult to reason with, sir.
translation.es: Creí que me iba a disparar. Es difícil razonar con él, señor.

translation.en: Kid! You want your promotion?
You want Carol's desk?
Then get off your ass, get in there, and verify those violations.
translation.es: ¡Pues mueve el culo, entra ahí y confirma las violaciones!

translation.en: Ugh! Hair on your nipples!
- Bud? - Seth!
- Seth! - Shit.
- Bud! - Hurry up! Shoot it!
I… I don't have my gun!
- Give me my shotgun! -
I'm… I'm just an observer!
Your gonna be hors d'œuvre if you don't give me that gun!
translation.es: ¡Serás su aperitivo si no me la das!

translation.en: Shit! Shit! Shit!
Whoa! I'm sorry!

Oh, jeez. That was horrible.
These Juvie teeth ain't worth shit, but get enough of 'em…
translation.es: Estos no valen nada, pero si consigo muchos…

What's going on?
Oh, come on. No, no, I'm not okay.
- All right? Look at me! - What?
Vampires just tried to kill me.
You put a gun in my face, and now I just pissed my favorite fucking suit!
translation.es: Me apuntaste un arma en la cara, ¡y ahora me meé en mi traje favorito!

translation.en: Hey, hey. Relax. You did good in there. You did good in there.
Besides, everybody pisses themselves the first time.
translation.es: Además, todos se mean encima la primera vez.

translation.en: - Really? - Yeah.
- Did you? - No, I… No, I didn't. But listen, you did.
translation.es: - ¿Tú también? - No, yo no. Pero tú sí.

translation.en: Here, dry your eyes. Dry your eyes, okay.
You know what?
Put it on me. My bad. We bit off more than we could chew today.
translation.es: Cúlpame a mí. Fue mi error. Hicimos más de lo que podíamos.

translation.en: So why don't we go home, get some rest.
In the morning, we'll kick some motherfucking ass. Okay?
translation.es: En la mañana, les damos con todo. ¿Sí?

Let's get in the car.
What the fuck is that? What'd you eat today?
You know what?

translation.es: Siéntate atrás, así no manchas mis asientos vintage.

translation.en: - What, are you serious? - Damn right.
Come on. Gotta move.
Hang your leg out the back so we can air dry.
translation.es: Y pon la pierna por fuera, así se seca con el viento.

translation.en: - You forgot your man- purse. - Wait. That's expens--
translation.es: - Te olvidaste la cartera. - Eso es…

they release a gas that gets on you that other vamps can sniff out.

translation.es: - Cielos. - En la ducha, por todo el cuerpo.

translation.en: Be extremely careful. Don't get it in your eyes.
translation.es: Ten cuidado. Que no te entre en los ojos.

translation.en: And whatever you do,
translation.es: Y lo que sea que hagas…

translation.en: don't get it in your butthole. What happens in the butthole?
translation.es: - Que no te entre en el ano. - ¿Qué pasa si entra?

translation.en: I mean, it can't kill you, but… Jesus Christ.
translation.es: No puede matarte, pero cielos santos.

translation.es: Traba las puertas, no salgas de noche y…

translation.en: - Guess what? - What?
You're dried up.
Oh!
translation.es: GENIAL. RECOGE A PAIGE PARA LA FIESTA DEL VIERNES.

translation.en: - Oh God. It's okay. - I'm sorry about that.
- No, no, me. I got it. - It's okay.

translation.es: Fue mi culpa. No veía nada.

Uh, nurse, actually.
Hope you don't think this is weird, but you got a lot of scrubs.
translation.es: Espero que no te suene raro, pero tienes muchas batas.

translation.en: Yeah, I mean, I hate doing laundry, so I kind of just kept buying new ones.
translation.es: Sí, odio lavar la ropa. Así que vivo comprando batas.

translation.en: - Got out of control. - Okay.
translation.es: Se me fue de las manos.

translation.en: But, hey, new apartment. Why not start off on the right foot?
translation.es: Apartamento nuevo. Mejor empezar con el pie derecho.

translation.en: Yeah. Well, welcome to the building. I'm right there in 20.
translation.es: Sí. Bienvenida al edificio. Yo estoy en el 20.

translation.en: - Oh! Well, I'm Heather. I'm in 19. - Well, I'm Bud 20.
translation.es: - Bueno, soy Heather. Estoy en el 19. - Bud, en el 20.

translation.en: Can you help me with that, actually?
Oh. Yeah.
- Thanks. - Yeah, no problem.
- You can just put that down anywhere. - Sure. Okay.
translation.es: - Ponlo por ahí abajo. - Sí. Claro.

translation.en: - See you've got a retro vibe poppin', huh? - Mm- hmm.
- Dig that. - Thanks.
I wish I had a beer or something to offer you.
translation.es: Ojalá tuviera una cerveza o algo para ofrecerte.

translation.en: Uh, a previous tenant left some ice cream in the freezer, if you're interested.
translation.es: El inquilino anterior dejó helado en la heladera, si quieres.

translation.en: No, thanks. I'll take a rain check.
- You sure? - Yeah. Welcome to the building.
Thank you.
Feeling better?
Not really.
Got a little bit of that yellow stuff in my butthole.
translation.es: Me entró en el ano eso amarillo que me diste.

translation.en: It was so much worse than what you even described.
translation.es: Fue mucho peor de lo que dijiste.

translation.en: Bet it was.
You looking for something?
- Whoa. Hey, that's personal. - No, no, no.
Violation code 101, terminated vamps and didn't report to the Union.
translation.es: Violación del Código 101, no informó al sindicato matanza de vampiros.

translation.en: Violation code 276, breaking and entering without Union sanctions.
translation.es: Violación del Código 276, asaltar sin autorización del sindicato.

translation.en: - That did happen. - Violation. Violation. Violation.
translation.es: - Pero es lo que pasó. - Violación.

translation.en: Oh, look at this. Needs to reimburse me for six- dollar muffin?
translation.es: Mira esto. ¿Me debe $6 por la magdalena?.

translation.en: It's a standard part of Union procedure.
- I have to document everything. - It's not.
It's for Seeger to keep me out the Union. Ain't that great?
translation.es: Es para Seeger, para echarme del sindicato. ¿No es genial?

translation.en: You almost got me killed yesterday.
translation.es: Casi haces que me maten ayer.

translation.en: You almost got yourself killed yesterday.
translation.es: Tú casi haces que te maten.

translation.en: I told you stay your punk- ass in the car. That's why I work by myself.
translation.es: Te dije que te quedaras en el auto. Por eso trabajo solo.

translation.en: Listen. What? You're gonna die in the name of kissing your boss's ass?
translation.es: ¿Qué? ¿Vas a morir por lamerle el culo a tu jefe?

translation.en: Well, he didn't give me a choice, okay?
Listen to me, Mr. Union Fellow.
I may not follow all the Union rules, but let me tell you something.
translation.es: No seguiré todas las reglas del sindicato, pero te diré algo.

translation.en: If we went by the book, we'd both be dead by now!
translation.es: Si lo hiciéramos, ambos estaríamos muertos.

translation.en: And you saw that yesterday.
Look. Just give me a couple of days.
translation.es: Escucha. Dame un par de días.

translation.en: Okay, a couple days.
So, what's on the agenda today?
Like every day.
Hunting vampires.
Bud, what are we doing at a pawn shop?
translation.es: Bud, ¿qué hacemos en una casa de empeños?

translation.en: This dude's cheap as shit, but he got goods we need in order to, uh…
translation.es: Es un desastre, pero tiene cosas que necesitamos para…

translation.en: What the hell?
Oh Jesus.
Shut up. Shut up.
Don't you puke in here! Don't touch nothing. Don't leave your DNA.
translation.es: ¡No vomites aquí! No toques nada. No dejes tu ADN.

translation.en: I swallowed it.
Troy.
Troy?
Damn it.
Wait, is that…
It was.
Oh no.
Who… who does that?
All right, we gotta move.
Wait a minute. Take this.
Are you kidding me?
- It's not right, okay. Wait-- - Damn right. How you think he feels, huh?
translation.es: - No está bien. Espera… - ¿Cómo crees que se siente?

translation.en: Come on, let's go.
Wait. You can't leave. That's against protocol.
translation.es: No podemos irnos. Infringe el protocolo.

translation.en: We have to call the Union and wait for them.
- Code 233 says any hunter who encounters… - Code? I don't give a shit.
translation.es: - El Código 233 dice que un cazador… - No me importa.

translation.en: …suspicious civilian death will be under a 30- day suspension--
translation.es: …que encuentre a un civil muerto estará 30 días…

translation.en: We don't have 30 days. I don't give fuck!
We gotta leave. There's other vamps around here. Let's go.
No, no. I'm calling.
Whoa! We have dead humans here. We have to report this.
That ain't no dead human! That's my friend!
translation.es: ¡No es un humano muerto! ¡Es mi amigo!

translation.en: Listen, I'm not telling you you cannot report it.
translation.es: No te digo que no puedes informarlo.

translation.en: I'm just telling you to delay it.
We'll make an anonymous call to the cops, and, after 24 hours,
translation.es: Llamamos anónimamente a la policía, y en 24 horas,

translation.en: you can make your funky little report. Let's go!
Why do you care? What difference does a day make?
I'm gonna lose my family in a day! That's the difference!
translation.es: Perderé a mi familia en un día. Esa es la diferencia.

translation.en: What?
Look, if I don't score some prices at Union wages by Monday,
translation.es: Si no consigo que el sindicato me pague para el lunes,

translation.en: my wife and my daughter move to Florida.
translation.es: mi esposa y mi hija se irán a Florida.

translation.en: That means, if you call Seeger, I'm gonna lose my family.
translation.es: Si llamas a Seeger, perderé a mi familia.

translation.en: I'm… I'm sorry.
Yeah, I bet you are.
